{"id": "byd-2026-04-24-019", "date": "2026-04-24", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 17, "weekday": "Fri"}, "entities": {"companies": ["byd"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": [], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "BYD’s luxury off-road brand unveils first electric sedan and a low-slung sports car [Images]", "content": "<div class=\"feat-image\"><img src=\"https://electrek.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2026/04/BYD-Formula-luxury-EV-supercar-1.jpeg?quality=82&#038;strip=all&#038;w=1400\" /></div><p>Fang Cheng Bao is best known for its high-end off-road SUVs, but now <a href=\"https://electrek.co/guides/byd/\">BYD’s</a> sub-brand has its sights set on a new market after revealing its first electric sedan and striking Formula X sports car.</p>\n\n\n\n <a data-layer-pagetype=\"post\" data-layer-postcategory=\"byd\" data-layer-vi", "sources": [{"name": "electrek", "url": "https://electrek.co/2026/04/24/byds-off-road-brand-debuts-first-ev-sedan-and-sports-car-images/", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "catl-2026-04-24-020", "date": "2026-04-24", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 17, "weekday": "Fri"}, "entities": {"companies": ["catl"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": [], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Hyundai unveils sleek new IONIQ V: a production car that looks like a concept", "content": "<div class=\"feat-image\"><img src=\"https://electrek.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2026/04/Hyundai-Vision-V.jpeg?quality=82&#038;strip=all&#038;w=1600\" /></div><p>Hyundai unveiled the IONIQ V at Auto China 2026 in Beijing today, a sleek electric liftback with over 600 km of CLTC range built on an 800V platform with CATL batteries. It’s the production version of the Venus concept the automaker <a href=\"https://electrek.co/2026/04/10/hyundai-unveils-two-ioniq-ev-concepts-car-suv-images/\">revealed ea", "sources": [{"name": "electrek", "url": "https://electrek.co/2026/04/24/hyundai-ioniq-v-china-600-km-range-auto-china-2026/", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "nio-2026-04-24-021", "date": "2026-04-24", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 17, "weekday": "Fri"}, "entities": {"companies": ["nio"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": [], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Nio launches special edition ES8, Onvo L80 debut set for Apr 28", "content": "<p><img src=\"https://cnevpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/2026042413184494.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>\n<p>The Nio ES8 Mirrorblack Edition starts at 456,800 yuan ($66,820) including the battery pack, which is 12.29% higher than the regular ES8.</p>\n<p>For details, please visit <a href=\"https://cnevpost.com\">CnEVPost</a>.</p>\n", "sources": [{"name": "cnevpost", "url": "https://cnevpost.com/2026/04/24/nio-launches-special-edition-es8-onvo-l80-debut-apr-28/", "type": "rss"}]}
